org.jcvi.jillion.trim.lucy

Class LucyQualityTrimmerBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.trim.lucy.LucyQualityTrimmerBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Builder<QualityTrimmer>

    public final class LucyQualityTrimmerBuilder
extends Object
implements Builder<QualityTrimmer>
    LucyLikeQualityTrimmerBuilder is a Builder that can create a QualityTrimmer that trims QualitySequences using the same algorithm as the TIGR program Lucy. The algorithm this class uses is the algorithm from the 2001 Lucy paper in Bioinformatics (link is below).

    The Trimming algorithm performs 3 separate trimming phases:

    1. The beginning and end of each sequence is trimmed to remove the low quality data from each end. The resulting region is called the bracket.
    2. The bracket is then trimmed against a series of sliding Windows. A Window of a certain size is slid across the bracket, if the average error probability of the data inside the window meets the given threshold, then that window is considered good quality. If more than one window is given,then the next Window is applied to the good quality range found by the previous window. The order of the Windows applied to trimming is largest window size to smallest window size. The resulting ranges from this step will be referred to as candidate regions
    3. Finally, the candidate good quality regions are further trimmed to meet overall error rates and the ends of the region (currently first and last 2 bases) must also meet a specific error rate threshold. Each candidate region is trimmed until each end and the total overall error rate meet these thresholds at the same time.
      4. The largest of the ranges after all these steps is the final trim range.
    Author:
    dkatzel
    See Also:
    Chou HH, Holmes MH. DNA sequence quality trimming and vector removal. Bioinformatics. 2001;17:1093-1104. doi: 10.1093/bioinformatics/17.12.1093.

      • addTrimWindow

        public LucyQualityTrimmerBuilder addTrimWindow(int windowSize,
                                               double maxErrorRate)
        Add an additional sliding trim window to this trimmer. The final trimmed sequence must meet the requirements of ALL given trim windows. This Builder will correctly sort the trim windows by size for the algorithm to work so users can add trim windows in any order without affecting the output of this trimmer.
        Parameters:
        windowSize - the size of this trimming window.
        maxErrorRate - the max error rate for all the qualities in this window size.
        Returns:
        this.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the maxErrorRate is not between 0 and 1 inclusive.
        IllegalArgumentException - if the windowSize is <1.
